<paragraph blockId="28.[311,1047,1055,1111]" box="[594,728,1087,1111]" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">
(
<figureCitation box="[602,719,1087,1111]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="29.[130,190,820,839]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,784]" captionTargetId="figure-208@29.[170,1128,133,784]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figure 15. Amiota (Amiota) jizushanensis Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. „ (see Figure 12 for further explanation)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657935/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">Figure 15</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[138,1185,1151,1207]" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis box="[138,252,1151,1175]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Vertical lobe of gonopod less sclerotized with two thin, apical processes (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="29.[130,190,820,839]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,784]" captionTargetId="figure-208@29.[170,1128,133,784]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figure 15. Amiota (Amiota) jizushanensis Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. „ (see Figure 12 for further explanation)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657935/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">Figure 15C</figureCitation>
); aedeagus less sclerotized, partly fused to paramere (
<figureCitation box="[821,964,1183,1207]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="29.[130,190,820,839]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,784]" captionTargetId="figure-208@29.[170,1128,133,784]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figure 15. Amiota (Amiota) jizushanensis Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. „ (see Figure 12 for further explanation)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657935/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">Figure 15D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[138,259,1262,1286]" box="[138,259,1262,1286]" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis box="[138,259,1262,1286]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[138,1185,1310,1369]" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis box="[138,206,1310,1334]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">Wing.</emphasis>
Wing with 
<emphasis box="[358,382,1311,1334]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">ca</emphasis>
21–22 minute, peg-like spinules on ventral surface of costal vein between R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[262,295,1351,1369]" fontSize="7" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">2+3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[375,408,1351,1369]" fontSize="7" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">4+5</subScript>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[138,1185,1406,1430]" box="[138,1185,1406,1430]" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis box="[138,186,1407,1430]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">Leg.</emphasis>
Hind femur with six long setae postero-ventrally; hind tibia with eight setae ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[138,1185,1470,1685]" lastBlockId="29.[125,1173,904,961]" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="292" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">
<emphasis box="[138,322,1470,1494]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Epandrium entirely separated laterally at mid-dorsal portion, with 11–12 setae near posterior to ventral margins (
<figureCitation box="[606,747,1502,1526]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="29.[130,190,820,839]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,784]" captionTargetId="figure-208@29.[170,1128,133,784]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figure 15. Amiota (Amiota) jizushanensis Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. „ (see Figure 12 for further explanation)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657935/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">Figure 15A</figureCitation>
). Surstylus glabrous on medial mesal surface, not expanded at postero-ventral corner, with five prensisetae on distal margin, and several thin setae on outer and inner surface (
<figureCitation box="[659,796,1565,1589]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="29.[130,190,820,839]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,784]" captionTargetId="figure-208@29.[170,1128,133,784]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figure 15. Amiota (Amiota) jizushanensis Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. „ (see Figure 12 for further explanation)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657935/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">Figure 15B</figureCitation>
). Anterior portion of hypandrium entirely thin (
<figureCitation box="[297,439,1597,1621]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="29.[130,190,820,839]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,784]" captionTargetId="figure-208@29.[170,1128,133,784]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figure 15. Amiota (Amiota) jizushanensis Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. „ (see Figure 12 for further explanation)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657935/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">Figure 15C</figureCitation>
). Parameres separated from each other, lobe-shaped, each with apically, much-sclerotized, pointed and laterally, less-sclerotized processes, and 
<emphasis box="[1093,1117,1630,1653]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="291">ca</emphasis>
eight sensilla on medial surface. Aedeagus separated into one pair of small rods, each fused to base of paramere; outer membrane undeveloped (
<figureCitation box="[714,894,904,928]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="29.[130,190,820,839]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,784]" captionTargetId="figure-208@29.[170,1128,133,784]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figure 15. Amiota (Amiota) jizushanensis Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. „ (see Figure 12 for further explanation)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657935/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="292">Figure 15D, E</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme: apical plate with 
<emphasis box="[326,350,937,960]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="292">ca</emphasis>
three pits on each lateral margin; stalk thick, long (
<figureCitation box="[958,1096,937,961]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="29.[130,190,820,839]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,133,784]" captionTargetId="figure-208@29.[170,1128,133,784]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figure 15. Amiota (Amiota) jizushanensis Chen and Watabe, sp. nov. „ (see Figure 12 for further explanation)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657935/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="292">Figure 15F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
