<emphasis box="[633,652,1323,1347]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="292">A</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[688,771,1323,1347]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="292">watabei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of paramere and aedeagus, but can be easily distinguished from it by the vertical lobe of gonopod with two thin, apical processes (with one apical process in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen &amp; Toda" authorityYear="2001" box="[704,787,1388,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Amiota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="watabei">
